# Docs & Workflow

## Source of truth

| Layer | Role |
|-------|------|
| **Linear** (`EventForge` project) | Active work — acceptance criteria, blockers, status |
| `docs/TASKS.md` | Roadmap mirror — checkboxes + `KRE-xxx` links |
| `docs/LINEAR.md` | Issue index, parallel tracks, MCP cheat sheet |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Agent conventions |
| `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` etc. | Deep design reference |

## Session start (Linear MCP)

1. `list_issues` with project `EventForge` (or `get_issue` if user names `KRE-xxx`)
2. Pick unblocked issue in current milestone
3. Read acceptance criteria from issue + relevant `.cursor/rules/`

## On issue complete

1. Mark Done in Linear (`save_issue`, state: Done)
2. Check matching boxes in `docs/TASKS.md`
3. Update ADRs only if architecture changed

## Doc roles

| File | When to read |
|------|--------------|
| `docs/LINEAR.md` | Issue index, dependencies, what's next |
| `docs/TASKS.md` | Phase progress, exit criteria |
| `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` | Pipeline, events, diagrams |
| `docs/TECH_DECISIONS.md` | Before changing stack |
| `docs/PRD.md` | Product scope |
| `docs/ISSUES.md` | Postmortems — append after non-trivial infra/CI/debug fixes (placeholders only, no secrets) |

## On non-trivial bug fix

After resolving a production-style issue (Terraform thrash, CI OIDC, hung apply, etc.):

1. Add a STAR entry to `docs/ISSUES.md` using the template at the bottom
2. Use placeholders — never real account IDs, ARNs, API keys, or secret contents
3. Link file paths and error messages; point to `docs/CICD.md` for setup details

## Phase exit criteria

Don't start Phase 2 until backend Phase 1 scaffold is Done (KRE-125). Frontend (KRE-128) is Phase 4, not a blocker for Phases 2–3.
